title: Maverick's Pan-fried Tempeh
summary: Maverick's Pan-fried Tempeh might be just the main course you are searching for. One portion of this dish contains approximately 29g of protein, 73g of fat, and a total of 1060 calories. This dairy free recipe serves 5 and costs $3.33 per serving. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 2 hours and 1 minutes. A mixture of madeira, bay leaves, soy sauce, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. To use up the vegetable oil you could follow this main course with the Blueberry Coffee Cake #SundaySupper as a dessert. With a spoonacular score of 57%, this dish is pretty good. Try Stir-Fried Flavored Tempeh with Pickled Melons, Cook the Book: Pan-Fried Mung Beans with Tempeh, and Cuban Fried Quinoa with Black Beans and Smoky Tempeh for similar recipes.
